Definition: be persistent, refuse to stop
Example: he persisted to call me every night; The child persisted and kept asking questions
Synonyms: noun, cognition, perseveration, act, perseverance, persist, adj, all, continual, persistent, attribute, persistency, persistence, hang_in, hang_on, hold_on, verb, stative, continue, be, refuse, to, stop, he, persisted, call, me, every, night, The, child, and, kept, asking, questions
Frame: 28
Category: verb.change
